openhmd
------------------------------------------
OpenHMD aims to provide a Free and Open Source API and drivers for immersive
technology, such as head mounted displays with built in head tracking.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.6.4-1
  libGL1-19.1.6-1
  libGLEW2.1-2.1.0-1
  libSDL2_2.0_0-2.32.8-1
  libhidapi-devel-0.15.0-1bl1
  libhidapi0-0.15.0-1bl1
  libnxjson0-0+git20200811-1bl1
  libopenhmd-devel-0.3.0-1bl2
  libopenhmd0-0.3.0-1bl2
  pkg-config-2.5.1-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-15-2
  automake-20250528-1
  binutils-2.45-1
  cygport-0.37.2-1
  gcc-core-13.4.0-1
  libGL-devel-19.1.6-1
  libGLEW-devel-2.1.0-1
  libSDL2-devel-2.32.8-1
  libhidapi-devel-0.15.0-1bl1
  libnxjson-devel-0+git20200811-1bl1
  libtool-2.5.4-1
  make-4.4.1-2

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/OpenHMD/OpenHMD/

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/OpenHMD/OpenHMD/archive/refs/tags/0.3.0.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack openhmd-0.3.0-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./openhmd-0.3.0-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/openhmd-0.3.0-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/openhmd-0.3.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libopenhmd0-0.3.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libopenhmd-devel-0.3.0-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(openhmd)
  /usr/bin/openhmd-openglexample.exe
  /usr/bin/openhmd-simple.exe
  /usr/bin/openhmd-unittests.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/openhmd.README
  /usr/share/doc/openhmd/LICENSE
  /usr/share/doc/openhmd/README.md

(libopenhmd0)
  /usr/bin/cygopenhmd-0.dll

(libopenhmd-devel)
  /usr/include/openhmd/openhmd.h
  /usr/lib/libopenhmd.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/openhmd.pc

